lace into refrigerator until ready to use. Clean and dry mixing bowl."},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Assembly"},{"content":"Cut baguette into 4 portions, and then slice each portion in half lengthways. Spread each portion with reserved pate and mayonnaise, then layer with pork, chillies, cucumber, Pickled carrot and coriander."}],"hintsAndTricks":["Bánh mì is a Vietnamese term for all kinds of bread. The word is derived from bánh and mì. Bread, or more specifically the baguette, was introduced by the French during its colonial period. The term is also used to describe a Vietnamese sandwich.","Ham can also be added to Bahn mi.","You can cover pate with extra melted butter to seal if desired. Pate will keep in refrigerator for up to 3 days.","Please refer to <i>The Basic Cookbook or Everyday Cookbook<\/i> for the Mayonnaise recipe.","Please refer to <i>The Basic Cookbook<\/i> for baguette recipe."],"basicInfo":["easy","45m","4h 35m","4 portions"]}